<refsect1>
<title>Compiling oiltest Applications on UNIX</title>
<para>
To compile a oiltest application, you need to tell the compiler where to 
find the oiltest header files and libraries. This is done with the
<application>pkg-config</application> utility:
</para>
<example>
<title>Compiles an oiltest "Hello, world"</title>
<programlisting>
$ cc `pkg-config --cflags --libs oiltest-0.1` hello.c -o hello
</programlisting>
</example>
</refsect1>

